{"session_id":"svc-1778991880575683390","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-17T04:24:42.273762064Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"opus","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"opus","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-0bc93861-20260517T042433-58489e63","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"fizeau-0bc93861\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eopenrouter: drop from candidate pool when credential or credit is missing\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;Fizeau\u0026#39;s auto-route includes openrouter as an eligible candidate even when no API key is configured AND/OR the account has zero credit balance. Dispatches that pick openrouter then fail at HTTP-call time with 401 (no auth header) or insufficient-credit errors. Beads burn retry cycles, sticky leases get assigned to a dead provider, and operators must debug a transport error to discover that the actual problem is a missing credential or empty wallet.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;This is the same pattern Fizeau already handles correctly for local LMStudio/MLX endpoints: when a local endpoint fails its aliveness probe, it surfaces as `filter_reason: \u0026#34;endpoint_unreachable\u0026#34;` in routing_decision and is excluded from scoring. Openrouter needs an analogous health gate.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;EVIDENCE FROM DOWNSTREAM (DDx, commit 09881f3a5)\u0026#xA;While debugging fizeau-80d4bf41 (auto-route candidate enumeration), I observed:\u0026#xA;1. With `--model sonnet-4.6` pinned, Fizeau routed to `fiz/openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.6` with score 196.0 (auto-route\u0026#39;s first choice once the model name was known to it).\u0026#xA;2. The dispatch then immediately failed: `agent: provider error: openai: POST \u0026#34;https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions\u0026#34;: 401 Unauthorized {\u0026#34;message\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;Missing Authentication header\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;code\u0026#34;:401}`.\u0026#xA;3. No upstream filter on the openrouter candidate. It appeared in the candidate list as `eligible: true`, was selected, and the credential failure surfaced only at HTTP call time inside the harness.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Symmetric symptom is expected when credentials exist but credit is exhausted — openrouter returns a 402/insufficient-credit response. Without proactive credit checks, every dispatch through openrouter will burn a retry to discover this.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;Add an openrouter provider-health hook analogous to the LMStudio aliveness probe. The hook should:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. **Credential check** (cheap, run on every routing pass or cache for a short TTL like 60s):\u0026#xA;   - If the openrouter API key environment variable / config is empty or unset → mark openrouter `eligible: false` with `filter_reason: \u0026#34;credential_missing\u0026#34;`. Do not even hit the network.\u0026#xA;   - If the configured key is malformed (wrong prefix, wrong length) → same.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;2. **Credit check** (more expensive, run periodically — recommend 5-15 minute TTL with stale-allowed-during-grace):\u0026#xA;   - Call openrouter\u0026#39;s `GET /api/v1/credits` (or whatever the current endpoint is) to fetch remaining credit balance.\u0026#xA;   - If balance is below a configurable threshold (default: $0.50) → mark openrouter `eligible: false` with `filter_reason: \u0026#34;credit_exhausted\u0026#34;`, include current balance in the decision evidence.\u0026#xA;   - If the credit-check call itself fails with 401 → mark `credential_invalid` (different from missing).\u0026#xA;   - If the credit-check call fails with transport error → mark `provider_unreachable` (transient; fail-open with stale-signal-penalty bump rather than hard-excluding, to avoid flapping).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;3. **Surface in routing_decision**: candidate row appears with `eligible: false`, `filter_reason` set to one of the values above, and `health_freshness_at` / `quota_freshness_at` populated from the cached probe. This mirrors how `bragi-club-3090` already appears with `endpoint_unreachable` and how `claude-haiku-4.5` appears with `power_missing`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;4. **Cache placement**: probe state should live in the same place as the existing harness aliveness/quota state so the route picker reads it without doing per-call network I/O. `service_routing.go` already has `health_freshness_at` and `quota_freshness_at` fields plumbed through — wire openrouter into that.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Multi-account credential rotation / failover within openrouter.\u0026#xA;- Per-model credit-cost forecasting.\u0026#xA;- The DDx-side change is none — this is purely Fizeau-side. DDx passes `policy=default` through unchanged per CONTRACT-003.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CROSS-REF\u0026#xA;Filed in tandem with fizeau-80d4bf41 (auto-route candidate enumeration collapses multi-tier subscription harnesses to DefaultModel only). The two bugs together explain why DDx\u0026#39;s `policy=default` lands on opus instead of sonnet: enumeration drops sonnet from claude, model-pin fallback routes to openrouter, openrouter has no creds.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. With openrouter API key unset (env var empty and config missing), routing_decision shows openrouter candidates as `eligible: false` with `filter_reason: \u0026#34;credential_missing\u0026#34;` and no HTTP call is made. Verified by an integration test that scrubs the env var, runs an Execute with no pin, and asserts the candidates payload.\u0026#xA;2. With a valid API key but zero credit balance, routing_decision shows openrouter candidates as `eligible: false` with `filter_reason: \u0026#34;credit_exhausted\u0026#34;`, and the candidate row carries the observed balance in the evidence body. Verified by a test that stubs the openrouter credits endpoint to return zero.\u0026#xA;3. With a valid API key and adequate credit, openrouter candidates are `eligible: true` and dispatch proceeds normally. Verified by the existing happy-path tests (no regression).\u0026#xA;4. Credit-check results are cached with a configurable TTL (default 5-15 minutes, exact value chosen by implementer) so per-request routing does not pay a network round-trip. Verified by a test that asserts the credits endpoint is called at most once per TTL window across N back-to-back Execute calls.\u0026#xA;5. A credit-check transport failure (e.g. openrouter.ai unreachable) does NOT hard-exclude openrouter — it surfaces as `provider_unreachable` with `eligible: false` for the freshness window but a fresh probe is attempted on the next routing pass. Verified by a test that simulates one transient failure followed by recovery.\u0026#xA;6. A 401 from the credit-check endpoint surfaces as `filter_reason: \u0026#34;credential_invalid\u0026#34;` (distinct from credential_missing) so operators can tell \u0026#34;you forgot to set the key\u0026#34; from \u0026#34;the key you set is rejected\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;7. Configurable threshold for credit_exhausted (default $0.50) is documented in the openrouter provider config docs.\u0026#xA;8. cd /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./... green.\u0026#xA;9. No regression in existing routing tests (service_adr005_test.go, service_routing_test.go).\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\ndecomposed into fizeau-458f10b0 (routing engine plumbing + filter-reason constants), fizeau-73a00a6b (credential_missing from env/config), fizeau-d6bed010 (credit-balance probe with TTL cache, credit_exhausted/credential_invalid/provider_unreachable, docs). Three deps-chained children: A → B and A → C, with C depending on both A and B. Each child lands as a focused reviewable commit; parent stays open until all three close.\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ekind:bug, area:routing, area:provider-health, impact:cost, impact:reliability, evidence:downstream-ddx, ac-quality:needs-refinement, triage:no-changes-unverified\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"e8e5a8642024ef1282b707d7766e3d4776d4b5b0\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260517T042433-58489e63\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-0bc93861-20260517T042433-58489e63/.ddx/executions/20260517T042433-58489e63/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-fizeau-0bc93861-20260517T042433-58489e63/.ddx/executions/20260517T042433-58489e63/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/